comments.body:
@edsantiago might be because you're not set as an org. admin in github (where bors gets it's permissions).

Assuming we get another timeout error.  At least Bors behavior is consistent between 'try' and 'merge' :smile: 

My guess is that it doesn't like the non 'success' or 'failure' status coming from Cirrus-CI (I marked some tasks as failure-tolerant).  After lunch I'll try removing that setting in `.cirrus.yml` but leave those names as optional for the bors status checks (in `bors.toml`).  That will bring back red-X marks next to some jobs, but maybe bors will (correctly) ignore them as configured.

Hrmmm :sweat: damn...I think this might be an actual failure (it's not clearing by a re-run): 

https://cirrus-ci.com/task/5183589830623232?command=integration_test#L961-L976

@edsantiago have you seen ^^^^ before?  It didn't seem to be a problem yesterday :confused:

> we know have manifests in specific formats

@nalind does that imply the tests depend on hard-coded references to metadata inside external content that we don't control?

Networking reliability aside, that makes me uncomfortable as it seems test-breakage would be both eventually-likely and unpredictable.

@cevich , new #2036 force-pushed, should handle the `images json` case.

@nalind, thank you, I'm trying to (ahem) digest all that. IIUC you are saying that those images are all hand-picked due to [certain characteristics], and that the test doesn't need to check those characteristics, it simply needs to guarantee that buildah doesn't crash when operating on them? I have one big question though:
> can successfully be pushed to somewhere other than local storage

AFAICT `digest.bats:fromreftest()` only pushes to local storage. Is that an oversight, or have I missed something?
